text: Hurricane Delta was an Atlantic tropical cyclone in October 2020. The hurricane struck the Yucat√°n Peninsula of Mexico. It later threatened east central Louisiana and western Mississippi. Delta's winds peaked near 145 miles an hour. The storm also threatened the western Caribbean islands, including the Cayman Islands, Cuba and Jamaica.
